This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image synthesis and style transfer. It may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it involves generating art-stylized images. Additionally, the use of a GAN framework and feature-map transformation technique suggests that it could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of experiments and quantitative evaluation suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
